Package Concepts

Class IndividualConcept

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • Concepts.Concept
        • Concepts.IndividualConcept
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataObject, java.io.Serializable

    public class IndividualConcept
extends Concept
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents leaf nodes in the concept hierarchy. Typical examples are concrete persons as sub-concept of the concept Person.

      • parseString

        public static IndividualConcept parseString​(java.lang.String identifier,
                                            Context context)
        maps a string to the corresponding concept. If a concept with this string as identifier is already in context.conceptPool then this object is returned. Otherwise a new IndividualConcept object is generated.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the string to be parsed (actually just the identifier).
        context - the context for the concept.
        Returns:
        either an existing object with this identifier, or a new IndividualConcept object.

      • parseIndividual

        public static boolean parseIndividual​(java.lang.String line,
                                      java.lang.String namespace,
                                      Context context,
                                      java.lang.StringBuilder errors,
                                      int lineNumber,
                                      DataBlock dataBlock)
        This method parses a single line with the information: concept individual_1,...,individual_n concept must be a known set-concept. If the individuals are unknown they are newly generated. The new concept/individual relation is inserted into the concept hierarchy.
        Parameters:
        line - the line to be parsed
        namespace - the namespace prefix
        context - the context for the concepts
        dataBlock - the origin of the data
        Returns:
        success or fail
